# deepscry-deploy.env — local, non-version-controlled deploy config.
#
# Copy this file to:
#     <parent>/.deepscry-deploy.env       (the dev harness root; preferred)
# or:
#     <repo>/.deepscry-deploy.env         (the mtg-forge-rs primary checkout)
# or:
#     ~/.config/deepscry/deploy.env
#
# Then edit the values below. The shared loader (`scripts/load-deploy-env.sh`,
# sourced by `scripts/deploy-cloud.sh` and `tests/remote/*.sh`) searches
# those three locations in order and sources the first one it finds. CLI
# flags / environment variables override values from the file.
#
# ABSOLUTELY NOTHING in this file is checked into the repository —
# `.deepscry-deploy.env` is in .gitignore. This file
# (`deepscry-deploy.env.example`) IS tracked as a template.

# --- Required ---------------------------------------------------------

# SSH login name on the remote VM.
REMOTE_USER=your-username

# Public hostname for the deployed site (used in the generated
# server-config.js so the landing page knows where the WebSocket
# endpoint lives — typically your DNS name, possibly proxied through
# Cloudflare).
REMOTE_HOST=example.com

# --- Optional ---------------------------------------------------------

# SSH target host. Defaults to ${REMOTE_HOST}. Override when the public
# DNS name is fronted by a CDN/proxy and SSH must go to the VM's real
# IP directly.
# REMOTE_SSH_HOST=203.0.113.42

# Remote install directory under $HOME on the VM.
# REMOTE_DIR=mtg-forge-rs

# HTTP port the unified axum server listens on. Default 8080 (works
# under both systemd-system and systemd-user modes).
# REMOTE_PORT=8080

# TLS termination directly on the VM (rustls). Leave unset for plain
# HTTP — typical when a CDN (Cloudflare) terminates TLS and forwards
# plaintext to the origin port.
# TLS_CERT_PATH=/etc/ssl/deepscry/deepscry.crt
# TLS_KEY_PATH=/etc/ssl/deepscry/deepscry.key

# systemd unit name (also used as the basename for the env file under
# /etc/default/<name> in system mode, or ~/.config/systemd/user/<name>.service
# in user mode).
# SERVICE_NAME=deepscry

# systemd mode: "user" (default — no root needed for deploy phase,
# enables lingering so service runs even when REMOTE_USER not logged
# in) or "system" (config phase needs root, deploy phase needs
# passwordless sudo for `systemctl restart <name>`). Privileged ports
# (<1024) require system mode.
# SYSTEMD_MODE=user

# --- Bug reports ------------------------------------------------------

# Optional password that marks submitted bug reports as "trusted".
# When set, playtesters who know this secret can send bug reports that
# trigger automated GitHub issue filing and Claude autofix. When unset
# (or empty), ALL reports are stored as untrusted — bug reports still
# work, but no automation runs. The deploy script warns (and proceeds)
# when this is not set.
#
# IMPORTANT: Keep this value out of version control. This file IS tracked
# as a template — the actual value goes in your LOCAL .deepscry-deploy.env
# (which is gitignored).
#
# TRUSTED_BUG_REPORT_PASSWORD=your-secret-here

# Optional egress-proxy wrapper for the server's `gh` invocations (bug-report
# GitHub issue filing) and Claude autofix. Normally LEAVE UNSET: a cloud VM has
# direct internet egress and runs `gh` directly. Set it ONLY on a network that
# requires routing outbound calls through a wrapper command (e.g. a Meta
# devserver's /usr/bin/with-proxy). `gh` must be installed + authed on the VM
# (`gh auth login`) for filing to succeed regardless of this setting (mtg-zvlpk).
#
# MTG_GH_PROXY=/usr/bin/with-proxy

# ── Login + cloud deck storage secrets — SEPARATE FILES (mtg-742) ───────────
#
# The GitHub/Google login secrets and the Cloudflare-R2 deck-storage secrets
# do NOT go in THIS file. They live in their own gitignored files alongside
# this one, so the high-sensitivity credentials are narrowly scoped and easy
# to rotate independently of the infra config:
#
#     <parent>/.oauth.env    — OAuth login (GitHub + Google)
#     <parent>/.r2.env       — Cloudflare R2 deck storage
#
# (The repo-root location `<repo>/.oauth.env` / `<repo>/.r2.env` also works as
# a fallback, same as for this config file.) Both are in .gitignore and are
# NEVER committed.
#
# deploy-cloud.sh SOURCES both files (fail-soft) and forwards whatever they set
# into the production systemd EnvironmentFile on BOTH `config` AND `deploy`. So
# the one-step enable flow is: populate the file(s), then run a normal
# `deploy-cloud.sh deploy`. Fail-soft means a missing/empty file simply leaves
# that feature disabled (the server reports unavailability) and never breaks the
# deploy.
#
# ── .oauth.env ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sign-in with GitHub / Google. A provider's button appears only when BOTH its
# client id and secret are present (server advertises availability via
# /auth/status). OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE is the public origin the provider redirects
# back to; the server appends /auth/callback/github and /auth/callback/google.
#
#     GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=...
#     GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
#     GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=...
#     GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
#     OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE=https://deepscry.net
#
# OUT-OF-BAND operator steps (one-time, at the provider — NOT done by deploy):
#   - Register the callback / redirect URIs in each OAuth app:
#         https://deepscry.net/auth/callback/github
#         https://deepscry.net/auth/callback/google
#     (must EXACTLY match OAUTH_CALLBACK_BASE + the path above).
#   - Rotate the client secrets before public launch.
#
# ── .r2.env ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-user deck collection store. When ALL FOUR are set, `mtg server-web`
# exposes GET /api/deck-storage/credentials, which mints SHORT-TTL, prefix-
# scoped PRESIGNED URLs the browser uses to PUT/GET its own collection.tgz
# directly against R2 — deck bytes never transit the server. When any are
# missing the endpoint returns 503 and the rest of the server is unaffected.
#
#     AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-r2-access-key-id
#     AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-r2-secret-access-key
#     R2_ENDPOINT=https://<account-id>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com
#     R2_BUCKET=deepscry-decks
#
# OUT-OF-BAND operator steps (one-time, at Cloudflare — NOT done by deploy):
#   - Apply the bucket CORS policy from scripts/r2-cors.json (so the browser
#     can PUT/GET cross-origin). Steps: ai_docs/reference/R2_DECK_STORAGE.md.
#   - Rotate the R2 token before public launch.
